If you have previously registered, but forgotten your password, <A HREF="http://www.eqatlas.com/cgi-bin/ubb/Ultimate.cgi?action=lostpw">click here</A>.
</font>

<P><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aieee!</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">One last annoyance from Aieee! ... for now.<P>Like everyone, I have to buy stuff like provision or arrows.  Stuff that I need in multiple quqntities.  For instance, I spent about 5 minutes buyng 100 arrows.  Click click click.  And BTW, it always seems laggiest when you are in a shop.  Anyway, why isn't there a wayt o buy a stack of 20 at a time.  Or if there is a way, how do you do it?<P>TIA,<P><P>------------------<BR>I am me,<BR>  <BR>Aieee!</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Oakao</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">also, why aren't quest items recognized if stacked? Why cant you create trade items more than one at a time? I'd like to be able to fletch 2 stacks of every componet into tons of arrows at once? Any why doesn't the message window have a way to page up and down?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kaneril</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">First, purchasing multiple items at the same time is coming. Not sure of timeframe though.  <IMG SRC="http://www.eqatlas.com/ubb/frown.gif"><P>Second, I don't know about creating multiple trade items at once.  Sounds like something that Verant wouldn't do though. (Just my opinion.)<P>And last, to page up and down in the message window just hit &lt;shift&gt;+&lt;Page Up&gt;/&lt;Page Down&gt;.<P>Kaneril<BR>Bard of the 16th Song<BR>Seventh Hammer</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">taobob</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">You are buying stacks of arrows&gt;????<P>Why on earth would you buy arrows when the ones you can make with even a minor Fletching skill are ten times better....<P>The only problem is that if you thought clicking to purchase arrows was tough, clicking the fletching supplies is twice as hard.... Imagine buying ONE stack of 20 of each of the arrow components (4).... That makes over 80 clicks, just to purchase them, and then aslo another 100 clicks to make the arrows (1 for each component, and then one on the combine window)... <P>We're just clicking our lives away....<P>I can see it now.... &lt;Verant Interactive had a Class Action lawsuit filed against them today, because of thousands of cases of Carpal Tunnel Syndrome&gt; Hehehe     <IMG SRC="http://www.eqatlas.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P><BR>------------------<BR>Blackivar Backbiter<BR>aka Blackivar the Cunning<BR>Halfling Rogue<BR>21st Season<BR>Druzzil Ro Server<p>[This message has been edited by taobob (edited 10-12-2000).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aieee!</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Why am I buying arrows instead of making them?  (Besides the click multipication, that is.)<P>Because the vendor in my home town does not sell fletching kits.<P>Because I am new to EQ and do not know where every vendor is that sells every item that I may be intereting to me.<P>Because I am a low-level DE and therefore might be KOS in the nearest town that does sell fletching kits.  (Whichever town that might be.)<P>Because I am nt sure that building up these trade skills every returns the investment it takes to get skill high enough to actually make things, reliably.<P>There reasons might not sound good to experienced EQ players, but they are reasons.<P>:-)<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Relevancy</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aieee!<P>good afternoon!  those are great reasons for buying instead of making, But if you are in Neriak, and I assume a DE is. (also new to the game)  They do have a merchant that sells fletching supplies.  I have never made arows myself, being a Shaman, and a Wizard, but I understand arrow fletching isn't that hard to do.   Look at the Atlas that Muse so wonderfully puts out for us, and it shows a fletcher for you to go to.  To check on your fletching skill, how to work it and what to combine go to <A HREF="http://www.everlore.com" TARGET=_blank>www.everlore.com</A>  and look under trade skills.  Every thing you need to know to suceed at trade skills can be found.<P>And then thank these people, Like Muse, who spend years compiling this information for us, in easy to access and understand form! <IMG SRC="http://www.eqatlas.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>Runteater</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">taobob</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">It will only cost you 2 or 3 practice points initially and that will give you a decent chance of success with the lowest class arrow that can be made... (I think I put 2 points in initially and was able to create arrows about 40% of the time)  The components for arrows are cheaper than the actual arrows, and they are better dmg/range even at the lowest combination.<P>The fletching kit can be kinda costly but it is worth saving 2pp for because of the money you'll save in the long run, and they sell the kits in Neriak from what I've heard...<P>Best bet is to investigate the trade skills, beacuse there are tons of sites with information on trades. You'll really need these skills at higher levels to make the good dmg arrows for yourself (that way you won't have to pay another tradesman to make some good ones for you), so it's best to start them when you're young... hehehe    <IMG SRC="http://www.eqatlas.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>&lt;Blackivar breaks another set of arrow shafts.&gt;<BR>&lt;Blackivar curses profusely.&gt;    <IMG SRC="http://www.eqatlas.com/ubb/smile.gif"><BR><P>------------------<BR>Blackivar Backbiter<BR>aka Blackivar the Cunning<BR>Halfling Rogue<BR>21st Season<BR>Druzzil Ro Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aanyia</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I agree that making arrows/bows is better than buying them in the long run. <BR>My 19 warrior just fletches when she needs arrows - only about skill 40, tops.<BR>That said, I was able to make a decent bow (with a couple of fails) and I make about 100 arrows before taking off on the next journey. <P>The neat thing about being an archer is if you're holding your sword (or whatever) and click on your bow, it will automatically put away the sword, take out the bow & shoot.<BR>By the time the critter gets to you, you click on your sword & start whacking away.   <P>Get in a group with Sow, & you're a puller extrodinaire - usually only stopping to check on the other folks mana. Believe me, when you offer to pull, the casters will be more than happy to let you do it & the healer will make sure you have plenty of health. <BR>If the casters have enough mana for the next wave & you sit down & say "need to heal a bit", the healer will top you off faster than you can type "ready for more?" <P>Go here:  <A HREF="http://www.westol.com/~ewj/fletchguide/" TARGET=_blank>http://www.westol.com/~ewj/fletchguide/</A> <P><BR>Aanyia Pointizz<BR>35 Druid<BR>Gathering Order<BR>Bristlebane<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Thisir</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hate to be the bearer of bad news , but the fletching shop does NOT sell fletching kits.  I've been there, several times, no go.  Go to <A HREF="http://www.eqtraders.com" TARGET=_blank>www.eqtraders.com</A>  they have a list of all the trade skills, recipes and locations for all the items you need for each trade.  The closest town to us that has a fletching kit is either Surefall Glade or South Karana.  I'm still low level myself, just getting lvl 9 in Shadow Knight.  I'm on the Drinal server so if ya want maybe we can team up and attempt the trip.  From what I have read, it's kinda tough...</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Oakao</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">At last I can page up down in the message window. I guess I only tried SHIFT+&lt;Page Up&gt; with the page keys on the number pad. They don't work. The other ones do. Yea! Thanks for the clarification.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aieee!</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hi Thisir, and everyone else.<P>Thanks for the tips on Fletching.  The nice thing about DE's is that no matter what type of character, your INT is decent so you can pursue the trade skills.  I would like to get a Fletching Kit, but... I use my bow to make pulling easier.  So "better" arrows are of marginal use.  I'm just not sure it's worht the couple hours (RL assuming no death and CR)it would take to travel to get a kit.  I may eventually do that, but right now it isn't that high a priority.<P>Thisir, I would take you up on your offer to travel for one, but we are on different servers. Thanks anyway.<P>Looks like I am stuck clicking 100 times every time I need a new btch of arrows!  :-)<P><P>------------------<BR>I am me,<BR>  <BR>Aieee!</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
